##Special interview with Gao Wenbin: Psychological construction is particularly important during the epidemic

Lifeweek

Features an introduction to a magazine and the life he advocates.

Gao Wenbin, a researcher at the Institute of Psychology of the Chinese Academy of Sciences, is the director of "psychological intervention for SARS patients and medical staff" and "SARS psychological consultation hotline of the Institute of Psychology of the Chinese Academy of Sciences" in Xiaotangshan, Beijing, in 2003.
In an interview with this newspaper, he believed that the new epidemic situation, in particular, needs to strengthen psychological guidance and intervention at the social level, "In 2003, direct expenditure on health care caused by SARS accounted for only a small part of the overall socio-economic losses, while the other major part, including related life, production and other economic activities affected by it, was caused by a series of chain reactions from individuals to social groups, as well as inappropriate psychological behaviour. "
By Lu Chen

"

By Lu Chen

Sanlian Life Weekly: Many of the medical staff in the front line of the epidemic have emotional fluctuations and even collapsed. Based on your experience during the SARS period, how to deal with it?

Gao Wenbin: After the serious public health event, the earliest intervention medical staff, because the rest time is insufficient, the replacement personnel is also insufficient, the work time is long, the intensity is big, a series of suppression, the fear psychological response will appear. The Wuhan situation is similar, so now the National Organization of forces in time to send medical teams to support.

Expedition photography

At this point in time, more medical staff will have two psychological problems. One kind is some medical personnel produces the psychology which gives up. At the time, in one of the first quarantined hospitals in Beijing, some medical staff pulled off their protective masks in the contaminated area, feeling that they couldn't figure out what to do anyway, so they might as well take a breath first, which was dangerous. Another is that health care workers question their own sense of worth. In many out-of-control situations, especially among young health care workers, this may seem like a futile and hopeless task.

Based on the experience of fighting against SARS, it is suggested that some experienced and trusted medical staff, such as senior head nurses, can play a good role in the team. They may not even enter the contaminated area, only in the peripheral change clothes, disinfection process to do some things, the same can play a demonstration and stability of the military role.

TRIPLEX Life Weekly: patients may appear some impulsive behavior when facing the situation of medical resources being tight and difficult to see a doctor. Is this a typical reflection of patients'psychological problems?

Gao Wenbin: I think extreme incidents are still rare. Although there are individual patients with impulsive behavior, but the face of non-cooperative treatment response should be better than SARS period. According to the experience during the SARS period, patients often do not cooperate because the description and expectation of the disease are not very clear, in addition to their own symptoms of illness, but this time because of the lessons learned from the past, the medical staff will explain and explain in response.

On the other hand, there is also a correlation with the age of the critically ill. Many severe cases during SARS are young adults, this age group is very active vitality, suddenly such a big contrast, their own not quite able to accept, easy to cause conflict. Although the data on this outbreak is not yet very accurate, based on the situation just this week, the patients with severe illness are mainly the elder and the younger children (the younger children tend to refer to the treatment of severe illness) , and the family members should be reminded to treat them rationally.

In order to deal with this kind of incident, we suggest that the hospital provides the specialized psychological help before the medical staff goes on duty and after encountering the emergency. In addition, mental health education must be carried out when patients are admitted to hospital. This part of work is usually also available in regular hospitals, but at this special time, it is even more important to tell the patient what is likely to happen, how to self-regulate, and how to find someone to help in case of a situation.

This new Crown Epidemic, patients with denial and avoidance and other psychological problems are more prominent, which is why many people run, or even hide the reason. This actually causes a lot of delay in treatment, and even more widespread contamination. If the patient can accept that the disease needs to be treated, he or she can return to a normal state of mind.

TRIPLEX LIFE: Can Emotional problems affect a patient's condition?

Gao Wenbin: we soon discovered that some patients'symptom aggravation or is unstable, and his emotional state has a great relationship. There are many crossed nervous systems in the human body, and inhalation is both the main symptom of the disease and the most directly affected by the mood of a set of systems. When the patient is fearful and nervous, he feels a sense of being out of breath. In fact, he is also out of breath, which exacerbates and confuses some of the states. So we sent a lot of material to Xiaotangshan Hospital, patients can regularly listen to 10 to 20 minutes, do their own inhalation training to assist treatment.

Sanlian life weekly: How did the psychological problems of doctors and patients improve during SARS?

Gao Wenbin: After Beijing Xiaotangshan Hospital runs really, the situation is much better. First of all, the basic material support is basically in place, and the flow is becoming clearer and clearer. Medical and nursing personnel are more and more beginning to think about some clinical individual diagnosis and treatment. Specifically, each patient's detailed plan. Patients are also psychologically prepared for their own conditions, everyone can go back to normal. Moreover, Beijing Xiaotangshan Hospital also transferred a group of Army Hospital Psychology Department, the Chinese Academy of Sciences and other institutions to help frontline medical and patient personnel.

Now, as far as I know, Wuhan Medical Staff with the team, there has been a psychological or psychiatric doctors. Wuhan Epidemic Prevention and control of the problem is still the first, but in the National Health Commission Disease Prevention and Control Bureau of the detailed diagnosis and treatment plan, the part of the psychological intervention has come out, the situation should gradually improve.

Sanlian Life Weekly: the spread of the SARS epidemic in Wuhan is more serious than when the general public has generated anxiety, how to alleviate?

Gao Wenbin: Now it is suggested that we wear masks, do not shake hands, a period of time in the past, it may be a habit, then we and the intimate way of communication will change. In particular, the public now regards Wuhan and even the entire Hubei region as "epidemic areas" , which will create a "psychological distance" for people from these areas, affecting normal social contacts. "Psychological Distance" is a basic concept of social psychology. The main influencing factors are trust, intimacy and security. If you translate that into physical space, you're talking at a different distance depending on how familiar you are with the person.

Most people don't feel much of anything right now, when it's strictly controlled. But after a while to start work, the office strictly guard, people's psychological distance suddenly increased, then your sense of isolation or insecurity will increase. So the relevant government agencies and large enterprises and institutions should start to deal with the COVID-19 in an orderly manner, providing at least one to two months of transitional guidance to help everyone balance work and life.

Sanlian Life Weekly: A lot of places still appear the situation that supermarket sweeps empty, mask snatches up crazily, how to do?

Gao Wenbin: If have not experienced this kind of sudden epidemic situation before, the public mentality is certainly very difficult to be stable. What the government can do is to guarantee and publicize basic materials and make a commitment to some of the necessities of life of the residents. In fact, the production of the whole country has not been significantly affected, normal material security is no problem, now the people demand is excessive.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Each supermarket, for example, has its own lead time, based on the usual volume. For example, the stock of salt may only be enough for people to buy evenly in a week, but because of the epidemic, people suddenly ran out of salt in one day, the stock cycle is not enough, the next day to go for sure or not, the panic then appears. The same is true of face masks. 1.4 billion Chinese used to wear them, but now suddenly everyone wears them. So the guidance of the social mentality needs to be specific, from the oil, salt, soy sauce and vinegar tea to guide, the more specific people more practical.

Sanlian Life Weekly: Now there are all kinds of overreaction in the society, like many areas in order to fight the epidemic, cut off all kinds of traffic arteries, what do you think?

Gao Wenbin: the social public's psychological problem, may divide into three stages. The first stage is when people start to feel uninvolved and defensive. The second stage is when they start to overreact. The third stage is when psychological problems start to increase and situations diverge, it doesn't even have to do with the outbreak.

Now we're in phase two. Two days ago, the Ministry of Transport and the Ministry of Public Security All came out and said not to cut off roads or obstruct normal transportation. This is because there has been an overreaction in society, and many places have cut off villages, counties and counties. We need to make it clear that physically breaking the road with obstacles, digging holes and what we now call suspension of public transport to reduce the spread of the epidemic are two very different things. In the absence of the relevant risks, road closure is of little significance, quarantine and identification of personnel should be strengthened.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In a country as big as China, transportation is not only an important component of economic activities, but also a necessity of life for everyone. The expansion of these self-insurance activities poses risks to the normal economy and life. It is still in the early stage of epidemic prevention, from the point of view of epidemic prevention must be strictly regulated, but everyone should start from their own to judge where the boundary of this degree.

The direct expenditure on medical care caused by SARS in 2003 accounted for only a small part of the total socio-economic losses, and the other major part, including related life, production and other economic activities affected by it, is the result of a chain reaction of excesses, from individuals to social groups, and inappropriate psychological behavior. So this time we have been emphasizing that psychological intervention is not only aimed at doctors and patients, from the perspective of public emergency, we should attach great importance to the psychological intervention of the whole society to help the public return to normal.

TRIPLEX Life Weekly: How does the public decide whether they should seek psychological intervention?

Gao Wenbin: First, if you focus too much on things, that is, if you can't not look at your phone for a minute, and you can't miss any new news, and second, if you have lost control of your emotions, if you've been feeling particularly anxious, tense, and out of Control Lately, and your normal pace of life has been disrupted, it's time to go to sleep, not to sleep, not to do anything. If you have any of these, I suggest you seek psychological intervention.
